## Stack

| Layer     | Technology                                            |
| --------- | ----------------------------------------------------- |
| Backend   | PHP {{PHP_VERSION}}, Laravel (nginx + php-fpm)        |
| Frontend  | Vue 2 + AdminLTE, Laravel Mix (Node {{NODE_VERSION}}) |
| Database  | MySQL (Docker service `mysql`)                        |
| Cache     | Redis (Docker service `redis`)                        |
| Packages  | csgt/utils, csgt/crud, csgt/cancerbero, csgt/menu     |
| Infra     | Docker Compose (`nginx`, `php`, `scheduler`, `horizon`, `mysql`, `redis`) |

## Local setup

Requirements: Docker Desktop (or Engine + Compose), git, and PHP + Composer + Node {{NODE_VERSION}} on the host — the `php` container image does not bundle Composer or Node, so dependency installs and asset builds run on the host.

```bash
git clone git@github.com:{{REPO_SLUG}}.git
cd {{PROJECT_NAME}}
cp .env.example .env && cp docker-compose.yml.example docker-compose.yml
composer install
docker compose up -d --build
docker compose exec php php artisan key:generate
docker compose exec php php artisan migrate
docker compose exec php php artisan db:seed
npm install
npm run watch
```

The app is served at `http://localhost`. If `APP_ENV=production` in `.env`, destructive Artisan commands (`migrate`, `db:seed`) require `--force`; set `APP_ENV=local` for local work.

