## Frequent commands

Artisan commands run inside the `php` container; composer/npm run on the host. The container shell ships aliases: `migrate`, `rollback`, `seed`, `seedgod` (= `db:seed --class=GodSeeder`), `cda` (= `composer dump-autoload`).

| Action              | Command                                          |
| ------------------- | ------------------------------------------------ |
| Artisan             | `docker compose exec php php artisan <command>`  |
| Tests               | `docker compose exec php vendor/bin/phpunit`     |
| Single test         | `docker compose exec php vendor/bin/phpunit --filter=TestName` |
| Frontend dev build  | `npm run watch` (host)                           |
| Production build    | `npm run production` (host)                      |
| Container shell     | `docker compose exec php bash`                   |

## CI/CD

The pipeline lives at `.github/workflows/ci.yml` (generated with `php artisan make:csgtci`). Every push and pull request runs code style, tests and the frontend build; pushes to the default branch additionally deploy to production when CI passes. The required repository secrets (`PRODUCTION_HOST`, `PRODUCTION_USER`, `PRODUCTION_PATH`, `PRODUCTION_SSH_KEY`, optional `PRODUCTION_SSH_PORT`, `PRODUCTION_SSH_KNOWN_HOSTS`, `PRODUCTION_HEALTHCHECK_URL`) are documented in the workflow itself.

